description: A group of arsonists sets local nightclubs on fire and Lois decides to go undercover at a club to investigate what is going on. Clark follows her steps and gets a job at the club as a bartender, also undercover. Johnny Taylor is the owner of the club but his sister Toni disagrees with the way he runs the organization and takes over after the club is attacked by the arsonists. Lex Luthor visits the club to meet with Toni and sees Lois singing on stage. Toni finds Lois and Clark hiding in the storage and Clark, to save at least his undercover, outs Lois. Lois loses her job at the club but she follows Toni and finds out that she is the one who is behind the arsonists. She asks them to stop now that she is running the club but the arsonists capture her and they keep their job. Superman manages to stop them while it is revealed that Lex also benefited from the arsonists as he was able to buy the land he wanted to build the "Lex Harbor" at a low price.
name: I've Got A Crush On You

series.name: Lois & Clark: The New Adventures of Superman

description: Four children, who seem to be very smart for their age, escape from the orphanage and they take over the city by appearing on TV and controlling everything. Back in the orphanage, a scientist named Dr. Carlton is looking for them. Lois and Clark try to find out where the kids are and why they are so smart. When one of them, Amy, goes back to orphanage to get her sister, she is captured and Lois becomes her temporary foster parent. Amy tells Lois about a portion that Dr. Carlton was giving them to make them smart but if you stop using it, you become dumb again. In the meantime, the rest of the kids find out that Clark is Superman but Clark manages to fool them that he is not. Later it is revealed that Lex works with Carlton but when the two of them disagree, Lex gives Carlton the new portion that, instead of making you smarter, it burns your brain. Lois and Clark convince Amy that her friends are in danger and she leads them to their hideout. They manage to convince all the kids that being a normal kid is the right way to live their childhood until becoming an adult and they all return to the orphanage where they are safe again.
name: Smart Kids

description: The Titans and the Little Buddies throw a surprise party for Birdarang and Beat Box. When the Titans leave to check out a crime alert, Cyborg tells the Little Buddies to keep the party going while they're gone. Eight months later, the Titans still haven't returned and the party is still going.
name: Brian

description: Robin brings Starfire on a fake stakeout in an attempt to get a kiss, while Cyborg and Beast Boy hold their own stakeout to discover Raven's dark secret.
name: I See You

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Moon Revived! The Mysterious Aliens Appear.

Japanese: Mūn fukkatsu! Nazo no eirian shutsugen (ムーン復活!謎のエイリアン出現)

Two months have passed since the Sailor Guardians defeated the Dark Kingdom. Having lost all memory of being Sailor Moon, Usagi now lives her life as an ordinary girl.
name: The Return Of Sailor Moon

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: For Love and Justice! A Sailor Warrior Once Again.

Japanese: Ai to seigi yue! Sērā Senshi futatabi (愛と正義ゆえ!セーラー戦士再び)

Sailor Moon finds herself facing new enemies from outer space, who call themselves Ail and An. The two aliens disguise themselves as humans to go after other human energy.
name: So You Want To Be In Pictures

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: For Whom is the White Rose? The Moonlight Knight Appears.

Japanese: Shiroi bara wa dare ni? Tsukikage no Naito tōjō (白いバラは誰に?月影の騎士登場)

Usagi, Mako, and Ami see a boy being attacked by one of Ail and An’s Cardian monsters. To Mako’s surprise, the boy turns out to be her childhood friend Shinozaki.
name: A Knight To Remember

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi's Crisis! The Tiara Doesn't Work.

Japanese: Usagi no kiki! Tiara sadō sezu (うさぎの危機!ティアラ作動せず)

Usagi goes to a virtual reality arcade that has just opened up in the Juban District, where she unexpectedly runs into Mamoru, as well as Seijuro and Natsumi.
name: VR Madness

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: A New Transformation! Usagi Powers Up.

Japanese: Atarashiki henshin! Usagi pawā appu (新しき変身!うさぎパワーアップ)

Usagi and her friends are enjoying the cherry blossoms, which are in full bloom, when the Cardian Leshy attacks them. During the fight, the Sailor Guardians are caught, and Sailor Moon loses her power to transform.
name: Cherry Blossom Time

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Targeted Kindergarteners: Venus to the Rescue

Japanese: Nerawareta enji! Vīnasu daikatsuyaku (狙われた園児!ヴィーナス大活躍)

Minako befriends a little girl named Mie who is a huge fan of Sailor Moon. Meanwhile, Ail and An send a Cardian to steal energy from young children.
name: Kindergarten Chaos

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Mamoru and Usagi's Babysitting Mayhem.

Japanese: Mamoru to Usagi no bebīshittā sōdō (衛とうさぎのベビーシッター騒動)

Usagi and Mamoru find themselves looking after a baby boy while his mother is recovering from having her energy stolen by a Cardian.
name: Much Ado About Babysitting

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The School Festival Is for Me?! Queen Rei’s Song

Japanese: Bunkasai wa watashi no tame?! Rei joō nesshō (文化祭は私のため?!レイ女王熱唱)

A school festival is going to be held at T.A. Girls’ Academy, which Rei attends. When Usagi and Ami go to check up on her, they find Rei busy overseeing the setup and events.
name: Raye's Day In The Spotlight

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Is Seijuro the Moonlight Knight? Mako-chan Falls in Love.

Japanese: Tsukikage wa Seijūrō? Moeru Mako-chan (月影は星十郎?もえるまこちゃん)

Ami and Makoto are trying to figure out who exactly the Moonlight Knight is. Suspecting that Seijuro and the Moonlight Knight may be the same person, Makoto volunteers to investigate by getting closer to Seijuro.
name: Food Fetish

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Steal Mamoru's Kiss! An's Snow White Strategy.

Japanese: Mamoru no kisu ubae! An no Shirayuki-hime sakusen (衛のキス奪え!アンの白雪姫作戦)

Usagi and the girls get into an argument over who gets to play Snow White in the upcoming play with Mamoru. After drawing straws, Natsumi gets the part, much to Usagi's frustration.
name: Mirror, Mirror On The Wall

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Be Careful After School! Usagi is a Target.

Japanese: Hōkago ni goyōjin! Nerawareta Usagi (放課後にご用心!狙われたうさぎ)

Usagi and Natsumi both get detention after angering Ms. Haruna during class. The two start working on their assignment when a Cardian suddenly shows up.
name: Detention Doldrums

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Disconnecting Love: the Raging Makai Tree.

Japanese: Surechigau ai no kokoro! Ikari no Makaiju (すれちがう愛の心!怒りの魔界樹)

Ail and An learn that the Makai Tree is beginning to die from lack of energy. Meanwhile, Usagi and her friends visit Seijuro and Natsumi's apartment after hearing that Natsumi is not feeling well.
name: Secret Garden

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: True Love Awakens! The Doom Tree's Secret.

Japanese: Mezameru shinjitsu no ai! Makaiju no himitsu (めざめる真実の愛!魔界樹の秘密)

While visiting Seijuro and Natsumi's apartment, Usagi and Mamoru come under attack by the Makai Tree.
name: Treed

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: An Angel? A Devil? Mysterious Girl from the Sky.

Japanese: Tenshi? Akuma? Sora kara kita nazo no shōjo (天使?悪魔?空からきた謎の少女)

A mysterious girl suddenly falls down from the sky, much to Usagi and Mamoru's surprise. Calling herself "Usagi," the girl demands Usagi to tell her where the Silver Crystal is.
name: Serena Times Two

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Huge Shock for Usagi! Mamoru Declares a Break Up.

Japanese: Usagi daishokku! Mamoru no zekkō sengen (うさぎ大ショック!衛の絶交宣言)

Usagi wakes up one morning to find that Chibi-Usa has gone missing. Meeting up with Mamoru, the two search the neighborhood for Chibi-Usa, eventually finding her sitting alone at the park.
name: The Cosmetic Caper

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Friendship of Sailor Warriors! Good-bye Ami.

Japanese: Senshi no yūjō! Sayonara Ami-chan (戦士の友情!さよなら亜美ちゃん)

Ami is offered a chance to study abroad in Germany, which would bring her one step closer to her dream of becoming a doctor. Knowing how important this is to her, Usagi and the others urge Ami to accept the offer.
name: Sailor Mercury Moving On?

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Women Should Be Strong and Beautiful! Rei's New Killer Move.

Japanese: Onna wa tsuyoku utsukushiku! Rei no shin hissatsu waza (女は強く美しく!レイの新必殺技)

Rei's grandfather is upset over the fact that Hikawa Shrine has had fewer female visitors lately. He then decides to retire as head priest to start a new business, which would allow him to be around young women, much to Rei's annoyance.
name: Gramps In A Pickle

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: In Search of the Silver Crystal! Chibiusa's Secret.

Japanese: Ginzuishou motomete! Chibiusa no himitsu (銀水晶を求めて!ちびうさの秘密)

Rubeus sends down Petz and her Droid to search and capture Chibi-Usa. Meanwhile, Chibi-Usa is calling someone on her Luna P ball telling her she wants to go home.
name: Trouble Comes Thundering Down

description: Team Avatar follows Aiwei to the Misty Palms Oasis, and Korra enters the Spirit World to find Aiwei and Zaheer meeting there. Disappointed, Zaheer throws Aiwei into the Fog of Lost Souls and explains the goals of his secret society, the Red Lotus, to Korra: an offshoot of the Order of the White Lotus, they want to overthrow governments to let freedom flourish in chaos. While Zaheer stalls for time, his allies close in on Korra's inanimate body. Bolin and Mako are overpowered, while Asami, fleeing with Korra's body, is captured by the Earth Queen's forces. The Red Lotus follows in pursuit.
name: The Stakeout

description: Yvonne Craig's 1st appearance in the series as Batgirl.
name: "Enter Batgirl, Exit Penguin"

deck: An impostor Batman wreaks havoc and frames the real Batman for his crimes. Bruce Wayne is forced to investigate the mystery behind this "Bad Batman".
name: Epitaph

deck: Jadzia falls in love with a scientist on a planet whose inhabitants shift between this universe and a plane of pure energy, re-emerging every sixty years. Back on DS9, Quark tries to obtain a holo-image of Major Kira for an erotic holosuite program for a wealthy patron.
name: Meridian

deck: Sisko, Jake, and O'Brien accidentally trigger an old Cardassian security system which believes that the Occupation is still going on and the station has been taken in a Bajoran workers' rebellion.
name: Civil Defense

deck: Ambassador Lwaxana Troi visits the station to attend the Bajoran Gratitude Festival, resulting in an outbreak of passion throughout the station as people admit their secret feelings for others.
name: Fascination

deck: When Commander William T. Riker from the Enterprise arrives on Deep Space 9, he takes a liking to Kira, who gives him a tour of the Defiant. But Riker is revealed to be not who he claims to be when he attacks Kira and steals the ship.
name: Defiant

deck: With history itself at stake, Sisko must risk all to see that the Bell Riots reach their inevitable conclusion, even if it means sacrificing his life...
name: Past Tense, Part II

deck: Trapped three hundred years in the past, Sisko, Bashir and Dax find themselves confronting one of the darkest hours in Earth's history...
name: Past Tense, Part I
Terror Tales of the Park II
